{{multiple issues| {{notability|Companies|date=April 2013}} {{primary sources|date=April 2013}} }} {{Infobox organization | name = | former name = | bgcolor = <!-- header background color --> | fgcolor = <!-- header text color --> | image = Pioneers_in_Engineering_Logo_1.png | image_border = | size = 250px<!-- default 200px --> | alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption = | map = <!-- optional --> | msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 250px --> | malt = <!-- map alt text --> | mcaption = <!-- optional --> | map2 = | abbreviation = PiE | motto = | predecessor = | successor = | formation = 2008 | extinction = <!-- date of extinction, optional --> | type = [[Non-governmental organization|NGO]] | status = <!-- ad hoc, treaty, foundation, etc --> | purpose = [[Education|Academic development]] | headquarters = O'Brien Hall, [[University of California, Berkeley]] | location = [[Berkeley, California]] | coords = {{coord|37.871766|N|122.26080819|W|display=inline}} | region_served = [[San Francisco Bay Area]] | membership = | language = <!-- official languages --> | general = <!-- Secretary General --> | leader_title = <!-- position title for the leader of the org --> | leader_name = <!-- name of leader --> | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | key_people = | main_organ = <!-- gral. assembly, board of directors, etc --> | parent_organization = [[Tau Beta Pi]] | affiliations = <!-- if any --> | budget = | num_staff = 106 | num_volunteers = | website = {{url|pioneers.berkeley.edu}} | remarks = }} <!--[[File:PiE_Staff_and_Students_Scrimmage_2012.jpg|thumb|200px|right|PiE staff and students in the 2012 PiE season.]] [[File:PiE_Season_Mentors_Students_Working_2012.jpg|thumb|200px|right|Mentors and students working.]] [[File:PiE_Season_2012_Tournament_Robots.jpg|thumb|200px|right|Tournament robots for the 2012 season.]] --> '''Pioneers in Engineering''' ('''PiE''') is a [[student organization|student-run organization]] that promotes the study of science, technology, engineering, and mathematics, collectively known as [[STEM fields]]. The organization was established in 2008 as a [[non-profit]] corporation by [[University of California, Berkeley]] student, Xiao-Yu Fu. The University provides training and mentorship opportunities for local high school students to improve their technological skills, by participating in a [[robotics competition]], during which each student team designs, builds, and programs functional robots.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://onedublin.org/2012/04/01/green-elementary-school-science-fair-inspires-student-scientists/ |title=Green Elementary School Science Fair Inspires Student Scientists |publisher=OneDublin.org |date=2012-04-01 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sfusd.edu/en/news/spotlight/2012-spotlight-archive/05/galileo-balboa-robot-competition.html |title=SFUSD: Galileo and Balboa High Schools Team up to Win Robot Competition |publisher=Sfusd.edu |date= |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Crawford|first=Amy|title=Robotics spark youths' math, science interests|url=http://www.sfexaminer.com/sanfrancisco/robotics-spark-youths-math-science-interests/Content?oid=2199093|publisher=SF Examiner|accessdate=19 July 2013}}</ref> Since 2008, over 20 schools have participated in the program.
==Background== Pioneers in Engineering was founded in 2008 by University of California, Berkeley student and [[Tau Beta Pi]] member, Xiao-Yu Fu. The organization's office is in UC Berkeley's O'Brien Hall. Staff members, including University of California undergraduates and graduates, design and assemble robotics starter kits for the competition, develop mentors for the program, and oversee public relations and internal communications.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pioneers.berkeley.edu/get-involved/join-pie-staff/ |title=Join PiE Staff · Pioneers in Engineering |publisher=Pioneers.berkeley.edu |date= |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> {{As of|2013}}, the organization has expanded to include 106 staff members.{{citation needed|date=April 2013}}
In preparation for the annual competition, robotic kits are distributed to groups of high schools students, who are paired with undergraduate mentors who assist the teams during the competition. A final tournament is held at the end of the season, allowing the student teams to reveal their work, for which awards are presented.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pioneers.berkeley.edu/programs/robotics-competition/ |title=Robotics Competition · Pioneers in Engineering |publisher=Pioneers.berkeley.edu |date= |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>
